com.ibm.team.build.ant.task

Class RequestBuildTask

  • java.lang.Object
    • Task
      • com.ibm.team.build.ant.task.AbstractTeamBuildTask
        • com.ibm.team.build.ant.task.RequestBuildTask
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IStaticReset

    public final class RequestBuildTask
extends AbstractTeamBuildTask
    Ant task to request a team build for a specified build definition. There must be an active engine supporting the build definition for a successful request to occur.

    Required attributes are:

    • buildDefinitionId - The build definition id such as 'Integration' to request a build for.

    Optional attributes are:

    • requestUUIDProperty - The ant property to store the UUID of the build request for the requested build. It will only be set if the build could be successfully requested.
    • resultUUIDProperty - The ant property to store the UUID of the build result for the requested build. It will only be set if the build could be successfully requested.
    • overridePropertiesFile - A path relative to the base directory of the build file or the full path to the properties file including the new properties or properties to override in the build definition for this request.
    • deletePropertiesFile - A path relative to the base directory of the build file or the full path to the properties file including the properties that should not be included from the build definition for this request.
    • allowDuplicateRequests - Defaults to true. If false, the build request will not be added if the build queue already contains a request for the specified build definition.
    • personalBuild - If true, this request will produce a personal build. Defaults to false.
    • buildEngineId - The id of the build engine which should process the request. Defaults to null, which means that the request can be processed by any supporting engine.
    See AbstractTeamBuildTask for additional required and optional attributes.
    Since:
    0.5
